  "text": "Isolation of MSCs directly from BM was performed, in cases 33, 34, 35 and 36, using a FACSAria flow cytometer (Becton Dickinson Biosciences-BDB-, San Jose, CA, USA), equipped with the FACSDiva software (BDB). Prior to sorting, cells were stained with a single four-color combination of monoclonal antibodies (MAb): anti-CD45-FITC (Miltenyi Biotec)/anti-CD73-PE (BD Biosciences Pharmingen, San José, CA, USA)/ anti-CD34-PeCy5 (Immunotech Coulter Company, Marseille, France)/anti-CD271-APC (Miltenyi Biotec), according to wellestablished stain-and-then-lyse-and-wash procedures which have been described earlier. [CITATION_1] The strategy used for the identification of MSC (CD45",
